 This time the task is to create a Day of the Week component.

---

## Task

Create a reusable Vue.js component that calculates and displays the day of the week (abbreviated) for a given date.

## Requirements
- The component must accept a `date` prop of type `Date`
- The component must calculate and display the day of the week abbreviated ([see list of all possible days](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Date/toLocaleString))
- The component must not waste any unnecessary computational resources

## Weaknesses to avoid

- Create a lot of helper methods, it will increase the coupling and complexity
- Use the `new Date()` many times and in places where the arguments are dynamic, it will decrease the performance.

---

## Solution

We will create a new component named `DayOfWeek.vue`.

```vue
<template>
  <p>{{ formattedDay }}</p>
</template>

<script>
  export default {
    name: "DayOfWeek",
    props: {
      date: {
        type: Date,
        required: true,
      },
    },
    data() {
      return {
        formattedDay: "",
      };
    },
    mounted() {
      this.formattedDay = new Intl.DateTimeFormat("en-US", { weekday: "short" }).format(this.date);
    },
  };
</script>
```

As you can see we pass the `date` as prop and get the formatted weekday using `Intl.DateTimeFormat`.

---

## Conclusion

This component is simple and easy to understand. It passes the date through the prop, does not waste any resources and calculates the day of the week using the `Intl.DateTimeFormat` constructor. We didn't need to implement any helper functions and became solution is reusable and decoupled.

