 I will look at the approach and help if needed. Here is a task: Implement a simple static stack using an array. Push and Pop method must be implemented, number of elements should be able to be checked, the stack should be able to grow or shrink automatically when needed based on element adding or removing.

Here is a solution:
```java
public class SimpleStack {
    private int maxSize;
    private int top;
    private int[] stackArray;

    public SimpleStack(int size) {
        maxSize = size;
        stackArray = new int[maxSize];
        top = -1;
    }

    public boolean push(int value) {
        if (top < maxSize - 1) {
            top++;
            stackArray[top] = value;
            return true;
        } else {
            System.out.println("Stack is full. Cannot push " + value);
            return false;
        }
    }

    public int pop() {
        if (top >= 0) {
            int poppedValue = stackArray[top];
            top--;
            return poppedValue;
        } else {
            System.out.println("Stack is empty.");
            throw new IllegalStateException();
        }
    }

    public int size() {
        return (top + 1);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SimpleStack myStack = new SimpleStack(5);

        System.out.println("Initial stack size: " + myStack.size());

        myStack.push(10);
        myStack.push(20);
        myStack.push(30);
        myStack.push(40);
        myStack.push(50);
        myStack.push(60);

        System.out.println("After pushing six elements, stack size is: " + myStack.size());

        myStack.pop();
        myStack.pop();

        System.out.println("After popping elements, stack size is: " + myStack.size());
    }
}
```
