My coding task is to write a JavaScript function that reverses an array.

Here's how I would solve it:

```javascript
function reverseArray(arr) {
  let startIndex = 0;
  let endIndex = arr.length - 1;

  // Use a for loop to iterate through the array from both ends
  for (let i = 0; i < Math.floor(arr.length / 2); i++) {
    // Swap the elements at the current start and end indices
    [arr[startIndex], arr[endIndex]] = [arr[endIndex], arr[startIndex]];

    // Move the pointers towards the middle of the array
    startIndex++;
    endIndex--;
  }

  // Return the reversed array
  return arr;
}
```

You can test the function by calling it with an array as an argument:

