Let's create a simple command line application written in C++ for a hypothetical interview, where we'll implement a function that calculates the length of longest common subsequence for two input strings.

## Problem Statement

For two given input strings, determine and output the length of the Longest Common Subsequence (LCS) using dynamic programming approach. Input will consist of two strings, the first string (str1) being smaller in length than the other (str2).

### Constraints

- Both input strings will consist of only lowercase english alphabets (a-z).
- The length of the two strings will not exceed 105 characters.

## Function Signature

```cpp
int lcs_length(std::string str1, std::string str2);
```

## Implementation

```cpp
#include <vector>
#include <string>

int min(int a, int b) {
    return a < b ? a : b;
}

int lcs_length(std::string str1, std::string str2) {
